div.p:
It gives me very much pleasure to acknowledge the receipt of your kind letter of the 22nd instant,
See M to H. Crummer, 22 January 1896. and to express my sincere thanks for the honor you have paid me by your courteous and lengthy reply to my remarks respecting the fate of Dr Leichhardts Expeditions;
See H. Crummer to M, 27 December 1895. and it is the more gratifying to me to feel that though burdened with the pressure of correspondence in connection with your onerous official duties that you should have condescended to tax yourself with additional labour in affording me full particulars of the information you possess which leads you to form a reasonable opinion of the causes that attended the fate of the Expedition.
